The paper deals with the computation of answer sets of logic programs, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also involves the use of graphs and colorings, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and logic (cs.LO). The paper is published in the journal Theory and Practice of Logic Programming (TPLP), which is a venue for research in programming languages and software engineering (cs.PL, cs.SE).
